Schizophrenia (SZ) is a chronic debilitating disease. Subjects with SZ have 
significant shorter life expectancy. Growing evidence suggests that a process of 
pathological accelerated aging occurs in SZ, leading to early development of 
severe clinical diseases and worse morbimortality. Furthermore, unaffected 
